== Role Overview

=== Position Details
- *Role Title*: Analyst (Corporate Advisory / Investment Banking)
- *Hierarchy Level*: Graduate to 2 years post-university
- *Division*: Mergers & Acquisitions / Equity Capital Markets / Debt Advisory
- *Institution Type*: Boutique Corporate Advisory or Investment Banking Division (Institutional Bank)
- *Example Firms*: 
  - Boutique Advisory: Barrenjoey, Lazard Australia, Greenhill Australia, Jarden Australia
  - Investment Banking Divisions: Macquarie Capital, UBS Investment Bank, Goldman Sachs Australia
  - Full-Service Brokers: Morgans Financial, Bell Potter, Ord Minnett

=== Position in Organisation
Analysts sit at the base of the corporate advisory hierarchy, reporting to Associates, Vice Presidents, and Directors/Managing Directors. They work across multiple live transactions simultaneously, supporting deal teams with:
- Financial modelling and valuation analysis
- Information memorandum and pitch book preparation
- Due diligence coordination and analysis
- Process management and documentation

