== Key Activities and Responsibilities

=== 1. Financial Modelling and Valuation (40-50% of time)

*Company Valuation Analysis*
- Build detailed three-statement financial models (P&L, balance sheet, cash flow) for target companies
- Develop Discounted Cash Flow (DCF) models with multiple scenario analyses
- Prepare comparable company analysis (trading multiples) across public market peers
- Conduct precedent transaction analysis for M&A deals
- Perform Leveraged Buyout (LBO) analysis for private equity transactions
- Calculate accretion/dilution analysis for mergers and acquisitions
- Model complex capital structures including debt tranches, preference shares, and convertible securities

*Industry and Market Analysis*
- Research industry dynamics, competitive positioning, and market trends
- Build market sizing models and growth forecasts
- Analyse historical sector M&A activity and valuation multiples
- Track recent capital markets activity (IPOs, equity raisings, debt issuances)
- Monitor competitor activity and public company performance

*Transaction-Specific Modelling*
- Model merger synergies and integration costs
- Build pro forma financial statements post-transaction
- Analyse funding alternatives and optimal capital structure
- Develop sensitivity analysis and scenario planning
- Model earn-out structures and contingent consideration

=== 2. Pitch Book and Presentation Material Preparation (20-30% of time)

*Client Pitch Development*
- Create PowerPoint presentations for new business pitches
- Develop detailed firm credentials and relevant transaction experience
- Prepare strategic rationale and transaction structure recommendations
- Format and proof complex slide decks to professional standards
- Incorporate feedback from senior bankers across multiple revision rounds

*Marketing Material Creation*
- Draft Information Memoranda (IM) / Confidential Information Memoranda (CIM) for sell-side M&A processes
- Prepare management presentations for company roadshows
- Create teasers and executive summaries for prospective buyers
- Develop data room structures and documentation indices
- Prepare Board presentations and transaction update materials

*Visual Design and Communication*
- Build compelling charts, graphs, and visual representations of data
- Ensure brand consistency and professional formatting
- Synthesise complex information into clear, actionable insights
- Tailor messaging to different audiences (Boards, management teams, buyers/sellers)

=== 3. Transaction Execution and Process Management (20-25% of time)

*Due Diligence Coordination*
- Manage virtual data rooms (typically Intralinks, Ansawr, or similar platforms)
- Coordinate information requests from potential buyers or investors
- Review and summarise due diligence materials
- Identify red flags and key issues requiring management attention
- Track outstanding items and chase responses from clients

*Transaction Process Management*
- Maintain detailed transaction timelines and critical path analysis
- Coordinate between client, lawyers, accountants, and other advisors
- Prepare Board papers and shareholder circulars
- Manage bid processes including indicative and binding offer stages
- Prepare comparison matrices of competing bids or financing proposals
- Draft term sheets and heads of agreement

*Regulatory and Compliance Support*
- Assist with ASIC regulatory filings and ASX announcements
- Support takeover documentation preparation (target's statements, bidder's statements)
- Prepare materials for Takeovers Panel and FIRB (Foreign Investment Review Board) submissions
- Coordinate with legal counsel on disclosure requirements

=== 4. Research and Market Intelligence (5-10% of time)

*Target Identification and Screening*
- Build target lists for buy-side M&A mandates
- Screen companies based on financial criteria, strategic fit, and ownership structure
- Research potential buyers for sell-side processes
- Identify potential investors for capital raising transactions
- Track industry consolidation trends and potential merger partners

*Market Monitoring*
- Monitor ASX announcements, company results, and material developments
- Track competitor transaction activity and league tables
- Follow regulatory changes affecting M&A and capital markets
- Build and maintain industry contact databases

