== Required Skills

=== Technical Skills

*Financial Modelling Excellence*
- Expert-level Excel proficiency (keyboard shortcuts, formula auditing, model best practices)
- Three-statement financial model construction and integration
- Advanced valuation methodologies (DCF, trading comps, transaction comps, LBO)
- Understanding of corporate finance theory (WACC, capital structure, cost of equity)
- Ability to build flexible, error-resistant models under time pressure

*Accounting and Financial Analysis*
- Strong understanding of financial statements and accounting principles (AASB/IFRS)
- Ability to identify accounting adjustments (normalisation, one-offs, non-recurring items)
- Understanding of working capital dynamics and cash flow generation
- Knowledge of revenue recognition, depreciation policies, and off-balance-sheet items
- Familiarity with financial metrics (EBITDA, EBIT, NPAT, Free Cash Flow, Return on Capital)

*PowerPoint and Presentation Design*
- Advanced PowerPoint skills (custom layouts, chart creation, alignment and formatting)
- Visual communication and data visualisation best practices
- Ability to synthesise complex information into clear executive summaries
- Understanding of corporate branding and professional document standards
- Speed and accuracy in high-pressure formatting situations

*Industry and Market Knowledge*
- Understanding of Australian M&A market dynamics and key players
- Knowledge of recent transactions and valuation trends
- Familiarity with industry-specific value drivers and KPIs
- Awareness of Australian business landscape and major corporates

=== Regulatory Knowledge

*Australian M&A Regulatory Framework*
- *Corporations Act*: Understanding of takeover provisions (Chapter 6), scheme of arrangement mechanics, related party transactions
- *ASIC*: Continuous disclosure obligations, misleading conduct, regulatory relief applications
- *ASX Listing Rules*: Shareholder approval thresholds, ASX announcements, trading halts, class order relief
- *Takeovers Panel*: Understanding of unacceptable circumstances, bid conditions, offer terms
- *FIRB*: Foreign investment screening, conditional approvals, sector-specific considerations
- *ACCC*: Merger clearance processes, substantial lessening of competition test

*Capital Markets Regulation*
- Prospectus requirements for IPOs and equity raisings
- Fundraising exemptions (sophisticated investor, institutional investor)
- Insider trading laws and market manipulation provisions
- Market sounding protocols and information barrier management

*Corporate Governance*
- Director duties and fiduciary obligations
- Independent expert requirements and fairness opinions
- Board approval processes and special committee structures
- Shareholder engagement and proxy adviser considerations

=== Interpersonal Skills

*Work Ethic and Resilience*
- Ability to work extremely long hours during live transactions (60-80+ hour weeks common)
- Maintaining quality and accuracy under intense time pressure
- Handling multiple urgent requests simultaneously
- Staying positive and motivated through challenging periods

*Attention to Detail*
- Zero-tolerance approach to errors in client-facing materials
- Systematic checking processes for numbers, formatting, and content
- Catching inconsistencies across documents
- Obsessive focus on precision and professional standards

*Teamwork and Collaboration*
- Working effectively with Associates, VPs, and Directors
- Supporting colleagues during high-pressure situations
- Taking feedback constructively (often blunt and under time pressure)
- Contributing to positive team culture despite demanding workload

*Communication*
- Clear, concise written communication for emails and memos
- Professional phone manner with clients and external parties
- Ability to explain complex financial concepts to non-finance stakeholders
- Asking clarifying questions to ensure understanding of requirements

*Commercial Judgment*
- Developing "business sense" beyond pure technical skills
- Understanding client motivations and deal dynamics
- Anticipating senior banker needs and questions
- Identifying key issues and focusing effort appropriately

*Time Management and Prioritisation*
- Managing competing deadlines across multiple live deals
- Knowing when to escalate issues versus solving independently
- Estimating task duration and managing expectations
- Working efficiently while maintaining quality standards

