== A Day in the Life: Corporate Advisory Analyst

=== Monday, 9:00 AM – Arrive at Office
Weekend was busy – worked Saturday afternoon finishing pitch book for tomorrow's client presentation (mining services company considering strategic options). Sunday off thankfully, but checked emails twice.

Start day checking overnight emails:
- VP wants updated valuation model for industrials deal by 11am (thought this was due tomorrow – deadline moved up)
- Director needs charts reformatted in pitch deck – client meeting moved from Wednesday to today at 2pm
- Two new information requests in data room from buyer on retail transaction – need to forward to client CFO

Priority list for today:
1. *URGENT*: Update industrials valuation model (due 11am)
2. Reformat charts in pitch deck (due 1pm for 2pm meeting)
3. Chase client on data room queries
4. Continue drafting CIM for healthcare business (lower priority, due Friday)

=== 9:15 AM – Coffee and Quick Sync with Associate
Brief catch-up with Associate on industrials deal – clarify what needs updating in model:
- New revenue guidance from management (lower growth in Year 2)
- Revised WACC assumption (VP wants sensitivity at 8.5%, 9.0%, 9.5%)
- Add two new comparable companies identified over weekend
- Update transaction multiples with last week's announced deal

Associate: "Should take you 2 hours max – let me know if any issues. I'm in client meetings all morning so ping me on Teams if urgent."

=== 9:30 AM – 11:30 AM – Deep Work: Model Updates
Focus time. Turn off email notifications, put phone on silent.

*Industrials Valuation Model:*
- Update revenue model with new management guidance
- Flow through impact to EBITDA, D&A, NPAT, FCF
- Recalculate DCF with new cash flows
- Update WACC sensitivity table (8.5% / 9.0% / 9.5%)
- Add new comparables: Seven Group Holdings and Monadelphous
- Pull latest share prices and trading multiples from Bloomberg
- Update precedent transaction slide with new Coates Hire transaction
- Cross-check all links and formulas
- Document all changes in model change log

Model shows valuation range now \$850m-\$950m (previously \$900m-\$1bn). Lower growth guidance having an impact. Send to Associate with summary email highlighting key changes and valuation impact.

Associate responds within 5 minutes: "Thanks – flagging to VP that valuation range has moved. Might need to tweak Board messaging. Good catch on making sure we documented why."

=== 11:30 AM – 12:00 PM – Chart Reformatting Crisis
VP sends message: "Charts in Section 3 don't match house style – client is picky about branding. Can you fix before 1pm? Use the format from the Orica pitch we did last month."

Pull up Orica pitch from shared drive. Identify correct chart style:
- Specific shade of blue for bars
- Particular font size for axis labels  
- Logo placement in bottom right corner

Reformat six charts in pitch deck:
- Market size analysis chart
- EBITDA margin comparison
- Historical M&A activity
- Revenue growth projections
- Geographic revenue split
- Product segment breakdown

Check alignment, spacing, fonts across all pages. Run spell check. Send to VP at 12:45pm. VP responds: "Perfect – you saved us. Client is very particular about presentation quality."

=== 12:00 PM – 12:30 PM – Working Lunch
Order lunch to desk (Thai takeaway). No time for proper break.

While eating, respond to data room queries:
- Email client CFO with two information requests from buyer
- One is simple (requesting latest management accounts) – client can provide today
- Other is complex (detailed 5-year customer contracts) – flag to Associate this might take a week
- Update data room Q&A tracker spreadsheet
- Set reminder to follow up Wednesday if no response

=== 12:30 PM – 2:00 PM – CIM Drafting
Return to ongoing project: drafting Confidential Information Memorandum for healthcare services business (pathology network).

*Today's focus: Industry Overview section*
- Research Australian pathology market (size, growth, key players)
- Review Sonic Healthcare and Healius annual reports for market data
- Check IBIS World industry report for market statistics
- Draft 3-4 pages on:
  - Market size and growth trends
  - Regulatory environment (Medicare rebates, licensing requirements)
  - Competitive landscape
  - Key industry drivers (ageing population, preventative health, technological change)
- Create charts showing market growth and segment breakdown

Get about 50% done before next interruption.

=== 2:00 PM – 2:15 PM – Last-Minute Pitch Book Update
Director messages 5 minutes before client meeting starts: "Just realised we need to add a slide showing acquisition funding alternatives. Can you pull together debt vs equity split options quickly?"

Drop CIM work. Build quick slide showing:
- Option A: 100% cash (funded by debt)
- Option B: 75% cash / 25% scrip
- Option C: 50% cash / 50% scrip
- Show pro forma leverage ratios for each scenario
- Use template from previous pitch

Send to Director in 12 minutes. Director: "Great – in meeting now, will add if needed."

=== 2:15 PM – 3:30 PM – Return to CIM Drafting
Continue healthcare CIM industry section. Finish draft and send to Associate for first review.

Associate responds: "Good start. Need to add more on regulatory environment – NPAAC accreditation, quality standards, etc. Also, can you find more recent market share data? These stats are from 2022."

Note feedback for tomorrow's revisions.

=== 3:30 PM – 4:30 PM – New Project Kick-Off
Called into meeting room with VP and Director for new mandate:

*New Deal:* Technology company (\$50m revenue) seeking growth capital (\$15-20m raise)
- Client wants to understand valuation expectations
- Need to pitch to potential investors next week

*Your tasks:*
1. Build financial model from last 3 years actuals + management budget
2. Prepare comparable company analysis (ASX-listed tech companies + offshore peers)
3. Draft investment highlights for teaser document
4. Create preliminary valuation range

*Timeline:* 
- Model due Wednesday morning
- Pitch deck first draft Friday
- Client meeting Monday

VP: "This will be your main focus for the rest of the week. Drop lower priority items if needed. Let me know if you need help accessing information – I'll intro you to the CFO."

=== 4:30 PM – 6:00 PM – Tech Deal: Initial Model Build
Get started on tech company model:

*Information Gathering:*
- Download financial information from shared folder (3 years of actuals, management FY25 budget)
- Review business description and investor presentation to understand revenue model (SaaS recurring revenue + implementation fees)
- Email CFO introducing yourself and requesting:
  - Detailed P&L breakdown by revenue stream
  - Monthly revenue progression (to understand seasonality)
  - Customer cohort analysis (retention rates, churn)
  - Detailed cost breakdown

*Model Shell Construction:*
- Build model template with standard structure:
  - Assumptions page
  - Historical financials (3 years)
  - Forecast financials (5 years)
  - DCF valuation
  - Trading comps
- Input historical actuals from provided financials
- Set up basic revenue build (Annual Recurring Revenue + New Sales + Churn)
- Create placeholder assumptions for key drivers

Make good progress but need more information from CFO before continuing. Send detailed information request email.

=== 6:00 PM – 6:30 PM – Admin and Email Catch-Up
Clear inbox and administrative tasks:
- Respond to various emails from earlier today
- Update personal task tracker with all current projects and deadlines
- Tomorrow's priorities:
  - Continue tech model when CFO responds
  - Revise healthcare CIM per Associate feedback
  - Build comparable company analysis for tech deal
  - Usual ongoing data room management
- File documents in deal folders on shared drive
- Update team availability calendar

=== 6:30 PM – 8:30 PM – Pitch Book Finalization
VP messages: "Client loved the meeting. Want to move forward with full sell-side process. Need to finalize pitch book for Thursday Board meeting. Can you stay to help finish?"

Work with Associate and VP on final pitch deck:
- Update all numbers based on today's discussion
- Add three new sections client requested:
  - Competitor acquisition analysis
  - International expansion options
  - Management retention structure
- Proof entire document (85 slides)
- Check all page numbers, headers, footers
- Final formatting pass
- Print test to ensure charts render correctly

VP reviews final version at 8:15pm: "Great work team. Send to client tonight so they have tomorrow to review."

=== 8:30 PM – Heading Home
Order Uber home. Exhausted but satisfied – got a lot done today.

Quick dinner (leftover pasta), respond to a few non-urgent emails, set alarm for 7:30am tomorrow.

*Evening reflection:*
- Long day (11.5 hours) but not unusual
- Juggled 4 different deals simultaneously  
- Felt good solving the chart reformatting crisis quickly
- Excited about new tech deal – will be interesting sector to learn
- A bit stressed about Friday CIM deadline – will need at least one late night this week

Check phone before bed – email from Director at 9:45pm:

"Great work today on the industrials model update. Client appreciated the quick turnaround. Also – heads up that tech deal client wants to move faster, so let's aim to have first draft pitch by Thursday EOD instead of Friday. Let me know if you need help prioritizing."

Adjust tomorrow's plan mentally. Welcome to corporate advisory.

